Overview

DeDuplicateArray project is created to remove duplicate values from input array. Various implementations are created to perform remove duplicate operations on input array End user can select any one of the implementations based on environment memory, performance and volume. This project build on Eclipse Neon IDE.

Environment Requirements for this package to use

  • Java 8

Build tools

  • Maven

Note : As we are using maven, all the dependencies are getting from maven global repository, In some networks, local repository will be used to get the dependencies instead of global repository, if we don't have access to global repository or maven is not able to get the dependencies from global repository in your network, don't use the maven tool to build and test the application, In this case, please use eclipse "Run As" command, I had included the same libraries which are part of maven dependencies to ensure the same.

Maven comments and environment setup

  • Please set Java Home path to Java 8
  • Navigate to project cloned directory from GitHub
  • execute mvn clean install to complete the build and execute the jUnit test cases
